There is currently no clean solution available to override the preference regarding MIME types of the displays on the stack, except turning `showable` on and off for certain MIME types, which means pretending that certain types are not supported at all and can lead to other issues. For example, just because a user wants to have png output in the plot pane, that doesn't mean Makie should tell FileIO or similar packages that it can't handle svg output.

